-- Apple’s Forstall, Schiller to Testify at Samsung Patent Trial
-- B y   A d a m   S a t a r i a n o
-- 2012-07-26T00:39:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/apple-s-forstall-schiller-to-testify-at-samsung-patent-trial.html
Apple Inc. (AAPL)  senior executives Scott
Forstall and  Phil Schiller  are among the officials the company
said will be called to testify at a patent trial against Samsung
Electronic Co. set to begin next week.  Forstall, the senior vice president in charge of the
software that runs on Apple’s iPhone and iPad, and Schiller, the
senior executive in charge of marketing, were on a witness list
provided by Apple.  At the trial, Cupertino, California-based Apple, and Suwon,
South Korea-based Samsung, the world’s two biggest makers of
smartphones, accuse each other of copying designs and technology
for mobile devices. The trial is set to begin July 30.  The case is Apple Inc. v. Samsung  Electronics Co. Ltd.,
11-cv-1846, U.S. District Court, Northern District of California  (San Jose).  To contact the reporter on this story:
